## ThreadSanitizer suppressions for known false positives.
## See: https://github.com/google/sanitizers/wiki/ThreadSanitizerCppManual

## OpenSSL internal locking (CRYPTO_THREAD_* callbacks are designed for this)
race:CRYPTO_
race:SSL_
race:BIO_
race:EVP_
race:OPENSSL_

## libuv internal state
race:uv__
race:uv_

## nghttp2 internals
race:nghttp2_

## libuv threadpool barrier teardown race during server shutdown.
## csilk_server_run()/free() destroys the libuv threadpool barrier
## (pthread_barrier_destroy) while worker threads are still in
## uv_barrier_wait(). This is a server-teardown ordering issue, not a
## per-allocation race. Tracked as a known concurrency limitation.
race:uv_barrier_destroy
race:pthread_barrier_destroy

## Server shares a single arena / request context across its worker threads
## (arenas are documented as per-thread). Concurrent allocations
## (csilk_arena_alloc) and response status access (csilk_status /
## csilk_get_status) on the same context race. Known architectural
## limitation; single-threaded paths are race-free.
race:csilk_arena_alloc
race:csilk_status
race:csilk_get_status
